		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>I was trying to run up a spreadsheet to compare dps on the new spells with my various foci. What I can't figure out though is how you factor in crits to the average damage. Any ideas?</div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
<br /><table class="tborder" cellpadding="6" cellspacing="1" border="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td class="page">
	
		<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
		<tr valign="bottom">
			<td style="font-size:14pt">Shoogie</td>
			<td class="smallfont" align="right">November 1st, 2006 04:29 AM</td>
		</tr>
		</table>
		
		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>Average Damage = (Probability of NonCrit)*(Average NonCrit) + (Probability of Crit)*(Average Crit)<br />
<br />
I'm not sure how often we're supposed to crit with new TSS AAs.  25%ish?  It would take a huge parse to figure out, which I haven't been able to do yet.  But I'll guess 25%.<br />
<br />
Average Damage = (0.75)*(Base Damage)*(1+(1+MaxFocus)/200) + (0.25)*(Base Damage)*(2.65+(1+Max Focus)/200))</div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
