		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>DPS is really not important.  The question is: how much damage I can do during the fight?<br />
<br />
Sothgar's Flame may be more DPS than Ball lightning.  However, If I chain cast SF, Harvest, Mod Rod, chain cast SF again and end up OOM before the mob is dead, then I chose the wrong spell.  I would have gotten more total damage with the more efficient Ball Lightning.  Take that idea to the logical conclusion, if it is an extreme endurance fight, then I can maximize total damage by chaining Chaos Flame.<br />
<br />
On the other hand, if the fight is so short that I still have mana left chaining SF, then I should have been using instant nukes.<br />
<br />
Lately most of my fights have been endurance fights.  My pattern has been to chain cast Sothgar's Flame until I am depleted enough to get a full harvest.  After that I switch to Chaos Flame, but mixing in Sothgar's Flames so that my mana drops at the same rate as the mob's hps.  Hopefully they should both reach 0 at the same time.  Of course, mod rod and harvest as soon as they are available.<br />
<br />
Thanks to Kela's post, I realize I've been stuck in the &quot;fire is best&quot; tunnelvision.  I think I'll be using Ball Lightning quite a bit more from now on.<br />
<br />
--Shoogie</div>
	</td>
</tr>
