		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>When I look at numbers I tend to just look at base numbers and when I think about focuses I just take whatever % focus and divide it in half and assume that number will be used.  I also don't think about crits.<br />
<br />
With DK / DP focuses:<br />
Ball Lightning Rk. ii - 4203, 809 mana, 7.0 sec - level 72, focuses undegraded<br />
5568.975, 647.2 mana, 4.1 second cast time<br />
DPS - 1358, DPM - 8.605<br />
<br />
Sothgar's Flame Rk. ii - 4900, 986 mana, 8.0 sec - level 75, focuses degraded 3 levels<br />
0.2*(0.95)(0.95)(0.95) = 0.171475 ,  (1-0.171475)*986 =  816.92565 mana<br />
0.65*(0.9)(0.9)(0.9)=0.47385 / 2 = 0.236925 * 4900 + 4900 =  6060.9325<br />
4.9 sec cast time (shown)<br />
DPS - 1236.925, DPM - 7.419<br />
<br />
Obviously if you're having difficulty landing magic nukes, you'll have to try another approach but on average I haven't found very many places that magic doesn't work.  The most difficulty that I've had with it was this afternoon on a quick jaunt through Anguish.<br />
<br />
Carlos case may or may not be different.  He'll take two hits of 10% on his magic focus or three hits on his fire.  Also have to keep in mind mana preservation and spell haste which are also taking hits.  Picking up new fire focus might even out the DPS but you'd still have a lower mana efficiency</div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
